description.p:
This object is achieved by a method for preparing single-sized II-VI semiconductor nanacrystals comprising the steps:
a) providing a first solution which comprises at least one group II B element precursor, at least one carboxylic acid and at least one alkene;
b) providing a second solution which comprises at least one group VI. A element precursor and at least one secondary phosphine;
c) mixing the first solution and the second solution to obtain a reaction mixture; and
d) heating the reaction mixture to obtain a solution containing the single-sized II-VI semiconductor nanocrystals. wherein the carboxylic acid: group II B element precursor molar ratio is 3 or less, preferably 2 or less; and
the group II B element precursor: group VI A element precursor molar ratio has to exceed 2, preferably at least 4.

claim.claim-text:
Method for preparing single-sized II-VI semiconductor nanocrystals comprising the steps:
a) providing a first solution which comprises at least one group II B element precursor, at least one carboxylic acid and at least one alkene;
b) providing a second solution which comprises at least one group VI A element precursor and at least one secondary phosphine;
c) mixing the first solution and the second solution to obtain a reaction mixture; and
d) heating the reaction mixture to obtain a solution containing the single-sized II-VI semiconductor nanocrystals;
wherein the carboxylic acid: group II B element precursor molar ratio is 3 or less, preferably 2 or less; and

the group II B element precursor: group VI A element precursor molar ratio has to exceed 2, preferably at least 4.
